Add x86_64-pc-makaos target support to libstdc++-v3.

libstdc++-v3/crossconfig.m4 has an explicit OS list; unknown targets
hit the catch-all *) at the bottom and get AC_MSG_ERROR("No support
for this host/target combination").  Add a minimal *-makaos* entry —
same shape as *-fuchsia* (freestanding, no hosted libc probes), with
section-splitting flags so the linker can GC unused bits.

We patch both crossconfig.m4 (the source) AND the generated configure
script — the build script doesn't run autoreconf, so configure needs
to be edited directly.

Signed-off-by: MakaOS <noreply@makaos>

diff --git a/libstdc++-v3/crossconfig.m4 b/libstdc++-v3/crossconfig.m4
--- a/libstdc++-v3/crossconfig.m4
+++ b/libstdc++-v3/crossconfig.m4
@@ -141,6 +141,14 @@ case "${host}" in
     AC_SUBST(SECTION_FLAGS)
     ;;

+  *-makaos*)
+    # Freestanding-ish MakaOS — relies on host-libc probes for hosted
+    # features via --with-sysroot.  Section flags give the linker room
+    # to garbage-collect unused bits.
+    SECTION_FLAGS='-ffunction-sections -fdata-sections'
+    AC_SUBST(SECTION_FLAGS)
+    ;;
+
   *-hpux*)
     SECTION_FLAGS='-ffunction-sections -fdata-sections'
     AC_SUBST(SECTION_FLAGS)
diff --git a/libstdc++-v3/configure b/libstdc++-v3/configure
--- a/libstdc++-v3/configure
+++ b/libstdc++-v3/configure
@@ -38409,6 +38409,11 @@ fi

     ;;

+  *-makaos*)
+    SECTION_FLAGS='-ffunction-sections -fdata-sections'
+
+    ;;
+
   *-hpux*)
     SECTION_FLAGS='-ffunction-sections -fdata-sections'

